Area Forecast Discussion
National Weather Service San Francisco CA
328 AM PST Sun Jan 14 2024

...New AVIATION, MARINE...

.SYNOPSIS...
Issued at 1221 AM PST Sun Jan 14 2024

Light rain ending this morning with quieter weather through
Monday. A weak weather system brings some light rain towards mid
week with rain chances returning for the weekend. Temperatures
will remain seasonally mild.

&&

.SHORT TERM...
(Today and tonight)
Issued at 1221 AM PST Sun Jan 14 2024

A dampening shortwave will progress from the Great Basin into the
Four Corners region as high pressure aloft builds in its wake. An
attendant surface front will dissipate this morning along the
Central Coast bringing an end to any lingering light rain. Clouds
may be slow to clear but temperatures should remain mild with no
real cold air behind the front. Look for highs right around 60 with
lows tonight dipping into the 40s. A few of the typically colder
inland locations in the Central Coast may reach the upper 30s.

&&

.LONG TERM...
(Monday through Saturday)
Issued at 1221 AM PST Sun Jan 14 2024

Dry and seasonal weather will prevail on Monday. A weak system will
bring light rain for Tuesday into Wednesday with minimal
accumulations. Quiet and mild for Thursday, with rain chances moving
back in for Friday into the weekend. Temperatures will remain mild
for the season with highs in the 60s and lows in the 40s to lower
50s.

&&

.AVIATION...
(12Z TAFS)
Issued at 328 AM PST Sun Jan 14 2024

The main rain band is exiting with some lingering showers in
southern portions of the area beginning to thin out. Pockets of mist
and fog look to linger in the North Bay into the mid morning. Cloud
cover lifts in the late morning, leading to widespread VFR with
scattered lower clouds and broken to overcast mid-level clouds.
Moderate westerly winds are expected in the afternoon followed by
northeast winds into the late night.


Vicinity of SFO...Becoming VFR with broken clouds around 3000 FT AGL
for much of the day. Cloud cover thins into the night and winds
become northeasterly.

SFO Bridge Approach...Similar to SFO

Monterey Bay Terminals...Lingering light rain lasts through the
morning with reduced visibility and IFR/MVFR CIGS. VFR returns with
moderate westerly winds into the afternoon, but mid-level clouds
remain. Cloud cover thins and winds become light into the night.

&&

.MARINE...
(Today through Friday)
Issued at 328 AM PST Sun Jan 14 2024

Calmer conditions are expected today as winds weaken after the
overnight rain. A quick moving cold front will bring more rain
and regenerate strong SW winds Tuesday with a longer period NW
following it.

&&

.MTR WATCHES/WARNINGS/ADVISORIES...
CA...None.
PZ...Small Craft Advisory until 9 AM PST this morning for Pt Pinos to
     Pt Piedras Blancas 0-10 nm.

     Small Craft Advisory until 3 PM PST this afternoon for Pt Arena
     to Pt Reyes 10-60 NM.

